<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00079</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROHIBITING RACIAL, ETHNIC, GENDER IDENTITY, SEXUAL ORIENTATION, AND RELIGIOUS DISCRIMINATION</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : The Anti-discrimination Act Of 2016</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to recognize the fundamental right of every person, regardless of sex, age, class, status, ethnicity, color, disability, religious and political beliefs, sexual orientation or gender identity, to be free from any form of discrimination, thereby intensifying efforts to fulfill its duties under international and domestic laws to respect, protect and fulfill the rights and dignity of every individual.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>AGLIPAY-VILLAR, EMMELINE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Welfare</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Villar (007 2016-08-08)</td><td>2. Sy-Alvarado (012 2016-08-17)</td><tr><td>3. Antonio (016 2016-08-30)</td><td>4. Abayon (018 2016-09-05)</td><tr><td>5. Tambunting (045 2016-11-16)</td><td>6. Batocabe (083 2017-03-15)</td><tr><td>7. Co (084 2017-05-02)</td><td>8. De Venecia (014 2017-08-23)</td><tr><td>9. Nieto (000 2018-02-06)</td><td>10. Arcillas (000 2018-02-06)</td><tr><td>11. Belmonte (R.) (000 2018-02-19)</td><td>12. Sacdalan (000 2018-02-19)</td><tr><td>13. Uy (J.) (000 2018-02-19)</td><td>14. Castro (F.L.) (000 2018-02-19)</td><tr><td>15. Kho (000 2018-02-19)</td><td>16. Alcala (000 2018-02-19)</td><tr><td>17. Lazatin (000 2018-02-06)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Deliberated upon by the Mother Committee on 2017-02-28</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>&n